<br>
Well Erana as it turns out there <!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><i> is</i><!--EZCODE ITALIC END--> no issue with Wizards farming. It's a hypothetical on this server at least.<br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE QUOTE START--><blockquote><b><i>Quote:</i></b><hr> Yep manaburn is only &quot;imbalanced&quot; in that they over-trivialize midrange raid content. - Gurunt<hr></blockquote><!--EZCODE QUOTE END--><br>
<br>
Yes well now we are getting to the meat. &quot;over-trivialize&quot; is a very good phrase to use. MB merely represents the leading ege of mudflation vis a vis Kunark bosses. A fact which I will grant merely because burners are so mobile. Not because 6 well equipped high AA toons cannot otherwise take out these bosses. It is certainly more convenient because there is no 'rounding up' necessary. But I feel this is also mitigated by the fact that if they fail, which <!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><i> does</i><!--EZCODE ITALIC END--> happen, they cannot try again.<br>
<br>
Nerfing MB would be unfair or else you would have to nerf all high aa toons against Kunark bosses to have equity.<br>
<br>
If you do that then people like ME who did not complete their epic until they had high AA would be screwed. Shall everyone who decides to level instead of working on their epic at 50 be therefore punished? Or do you give epics to everyone with high AA and then say ok <!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><i> from now on</i><!--EZCODE ITALIC END--> no one can kill affect these mobs if they have high AA? (ala Vox/Naggy)<br>
<br>
This make any sense?<br>
<br>
MB is bought and paid for. Nerfing it re Kunark bosses and not nerfing other high AA toons versus Kunark bosses is unfair. So you cannot equitably nerf the Manaburn skill you would have to:<br>
<br>
1) Say no high AA toons may attack Kunark bosses.<br>
2) Kunark bosses may only be killed if a certain minimum number of toons had engaged (affected or been affected by)<br>
<br>
Or something like that.<br>
<br>
If you will be intellectually honest you will leave MB out of it and address the real issue.<br>
<br>
The real issue is mudflation, and there is NO solution for it. They sell expansions BASED on mudflation. People expect to buy expansions and make their toons more powerful with some work.<br>
<br>
They have done so.<br>
<br>
Kunark is old. Sure Gore used to be tough, but she's yesterday's news now. She's a big white fluffy creampuff now.<br>
<br>
You can't look at MB, as arguably the leading edge of mudflation vs Kunark bosses <!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><i> only</i><!--EZCODE ITALIC END--> and say ok now we draw the line. Because then somethign else is now the leading edge of mudflation. Oh well now Warcry is terribly overpowered, nerf that, oh not Lifeburn is terribly overpowered, nerf that, etc, etc.<br>
<br>
And then whoever just got nerfed will be <!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><i> reasonably</i><!--EZCODE ITALIC END--> able to point at the next best thing and say 'hey you sodomized me why do you stop now?'<br>
<br>
And then what about PoP? Would you buy it if there was not stuff to make your toon better? No? Well then it'll be even worse. I certainly expect in PoP you wil probably be able to take gore with only 3 people, a well advanced Warrior, Cleric, and Enchanter.<br>
<br>
The whole POINT of high AA is to make your toon more powerful. This is so obvious but some people don't get it.<br>
<br>
It's really not soluble. There is no solution because they WILL continue to sell more powerful advancement opportunities. Last years expansions are old news.<br>
<br>
I certainly categorically reject any solution that does not similarly restrict ALL high AA toons against Kunark bosses.<br>
<br>
FK<br>
<br>
PS. I have a big problem with the way epics work myself. They should not be competed for by players against players and it should be a challenge to the player personally. Also ALL epic quest pieces should NOT be MQ'able. But that's another topic. But there ARE solutions to that problem. <p></p><i></i></td></tr></table><table border=0 width=95%><tr><td align=left valign="top">  Page <a href=http://pub54.ezboard.com/fquelliousquaterstherebirthfrm13.showMessageRange?topicID=323.topic&start=1&stop=20>1</a><a href=http://pub54.ezboard.com/fquelliousquaterstherebirthfrm13.showMessageRange?topicID=323.topic&start=21&stop=40>2</a><a href=http://pub54.ezboard.com/fquelliousquaterstherebirthfrm13.showMessageRange?topicID=323.topic&start=41&stop=60>3</a><a href=http://pub54.ezboard.com/fquelliousquaterstherebirthfrm13.showMessageRange?topicID=323.topic&start=61&stop=80>4</a><a href=http://pub54.ezboard.com/fquelliousquaterstherebirthfrm13.showMessageRange?topicID=323.topic&start=81&stop=100>5</a><a href=http://pub54.ezboard.com/fquelliousquaterstherebirthfrm13.showMessageRange?topicID=323.topic&start=101&stop=120>6</a><a href=http://pub54.ezboard.com/fquelliousquaterstherebirthfrm13.showMessageRange?topicID=323.topic&start=121&stop=140>7</a><a href=http://pub54.ezboard.com/fquelliousquaterstherebirthfrm13.showMessageRange?topicID=323.topic&start=141&stop=160>8</a><a href=http://pub54.ezboard.com/fquelliousquaterstherebirthfrm13.showMessageRange?topicID=323.topic&start=161&stop=180>9</a><a href=http://pub54.ezboard.com/fquelliousquaterstherebirthfrm13.showMessageRange?topicID=323.topic&start=181&stop=200>10</a><a href=http://pub54.ezboard.com/fquelliousquaterstherebirthfrm13.showMessageRange?topicID=323.topic&start=201&stop=220>11</a><a href=http://pub54.ezboard.com/fquelliousquaterstherebirthfrm13.showMessageRange?topicID=323.topic&start=221&stop=240>12</a><a href=http://pub54.ezboard.com/fquelliousquaterstherebirthfrm13.showMessageRa